  <prompt>
    Create the public-contract facade `IActionEngineFacade` in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` per ADR-013 refined 2026-05-20. This interface IS the binding boundary: every CRUD-side consumer of Action Engine capability MUST reach it through this facade. Do NOT inject `IToolHandlerRegistry`, `IActionOrchestrationService`, `IGateResolver`, or any Action Engine internal anywhere outside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/`. Create the interface + a placeholder skeleton impl that throws `NotImplementedException` until Phase 4 wires it up.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE BFF API designer experienced with the `PublicContracts/` facade pattern from ADR-013 refined. You design contract surfaces that are stable, narrow, and self-documenting — knowing every method signature here becomes a downstream dependency that's expensive to change once consumers begin using it.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Two files created:

    1. **`Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IActionEngineFacade.cs`** — the contract interface, with these methods (per spec FR-10..FR-12 + FR-16 + FR-17 surface):
       - `Task&lt;ActionRunDescriptor&gt; InvokeActionAsync(InvokeActionRequest request, CancellationToken ct)` — dispatch a known Action by id with parameters; returns descriptor (run id + initial state)
       - `Task&lt;ActionRunDescriptor&gt; GetActionRunStatusAsync(Guid runId, CancellationToken ct)` — poll run state
       - `Task&lt;IReadOnlyList&lt;ResourceCandidate&gt;&gt; FindResourcesAsync(string userIntent, int topK = 5, CancellationToken ct = default)` — semantic discovery (backed by Phase 2 meta-tool impl)
       - `Task&lt;ResourceDetail&gt; GetResourceDetailAsync(string resourceId, CancellationToken ct)` — full resource schema for a discovered Tool
       - `Task&lt;GateDescriptor&gt; ResolveGateAsync(ResolveGateRequest request, CancellationToken ct)` — submit gate approval/rejection on behalf of an external caller (used by Insights Engine consumption per coordination assessment)

       Plus the public DTOs referenced by these methods (`ActionRunDescriptor`, `InvokeActionRequest`, `ResourceCandidate`, `ResourceDetail`, `ResolveGateRequest`, `GateDescriptor`) — defined IN the same folder as record types, no Action Engine internal types leaked.

    2. **`Services/Ai/PublicContracts/ActionEngineFacade.cs`** — placeholder concrete impl. All methods throw `NotImplementedException("Action Engine facade impl wired up in Phase 4 (task 040+).")`. Class is `internal sealed` (CRUD callers must depend on the INTERFACE, never the impl). NO DI registration in this task (task 014 owns Program.cs / DI module; the registration of this facade impl is deferred to Phase 4).

    Deliverable: BFF builds cleanly; the interface + DTOs surface compiles standalone; the placeholder impl compiles but is NOT yet registered with DI (intentional — no consumer should depend on this in Phase 1).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      **ADR-013 refined (2026-05-20)** binding rule from spec.md §6 placement justification: "CRUD-side consumers reach Action Engine via `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IActionEngineFacade.cs` — NOT direct injection of `IToolHandlerRegistry`, `IGateResolver`, or other internal types."

      **Why facade-first**: the 2026-05-20 BFF AI extraction assessment (`docs/assessments/bff-ai-extraction-assessment-2026-05-20.md`) found 20 inbound CRUD→AI direct dependencies. ADR-013 refined was the remediation: every new CRUD→AI surface uses a public-contract facade. Action Engine is the first new AI-side capability shipping under this discipline.

      **What goes in PublicContracts**: only the public method surface + the public DTOs. NO Action Engine internal types (`Action`, `ToolDispatchContext`, `IGateResolver`, `PhaseRestrictions`, etc.) — these stay under `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/`. The facade method DTOs are flattened, stable, versionable shapes.

      **What this task does NOT do**:
      - Does NOT register the facade impl with DI (task 014 owns the DI module; the facade impl registration is deferred until Phase 4 has real wiring to expose)
      - Does NOT add `accessToken`/`token` fields to any DTO (ADR-028)
      - Does NOT leak Action Engine internals into the interface or DTOs

      **Coordination with task 014**: task 014 creates `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/` folder + `AddActionEngineModule.cs` + edits `Program.cs`. This task (015) creates only `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/IActionEngineFacade.cs` + `ActionEngineFacade.cs`. NO shared file edits — both tasks can land in parallel cleanly.

      **Why blocks Phase 2+**: every Phase 2+ task that exposes Action Engine capability to a CRUD-side caller (e.g., task 050 SpaarkeAi launcher consuming the facade) requires this interface to exist. Phase 1 ships the contract; Phase 4 wires up the impl.
    </background>
