  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">.NET 8 Minimal API conventions; record types preferred for DTOs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint-filter authorization. Endpoints that USE this facade (Phase 2+) apply `.AddEndpointFilter&lt;&gt;()`. This task creates no endpoints.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Feature-module DI. The facade impl is registered by `AddActionEngineModule()` in a LATER phase. This task does NOT touch DI.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 (refined)">CRUD-side consumers reach Action Engine ONLY via this facade. Internal types (`IToolHandlerRegistry`, `IGateResolver`, `ActionOrchestrationService`, etc.) MUST NOT be referenced anywhere outside `Services/Ai/ActionEngine/`. The facade is the only public surface.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Errors returned via the facade follow ProblemDetails RFC 7807 (when endpoints surface them). The interface methods themselves throw typed exceptions (e.g., `ResourceNotFoundException`, `PhaseToolDeniedException` reified at facade boundary).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">Spaarke Auth v2. NO `accessToken`/`token` fields on any DTO. Auth context flows via ambient request principal, not facade parameters.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta MUST be ≤ 5 MB compressed. For an interface + DTOs + placeholder impl, expect a few KB. Verify.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist binding: placement decision (BFF, per ADR-013 refined), ADRs cited, publish-size verified, no new HIGH-sev CVE, feature-module DI (facade registration deferred to Phase 4).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Facade impl class is `internal sealed`. CRUD callers depend on the INTERFACE; this prevents accidental misuse of impl-specific behavior.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">DTOs are records (immutable). NO Action Engine internal types leaked into the public surface.</constraint>
  </constraints>

